'''''Pushpa 2: The Rule''''' is a 2024 Indian [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]]-language [[action drama film]]<ref>{{Cite news |date=2024-10-27 |title=Has Allu Arjun surpassed Vijay to become the highest-paid Indian actor with 'Pushpa 2'? |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/has-allu-arjun-surpassed-vijay-to-become-the-highest-paid-indian-actor-with-pushpa-2/articleshow/114646487.cms |access-date=2024-10-27 |work=The Times of India |issn=0971-8257 |archive-date=27 October 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241027090103/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/has-allu-arjun-surpassed-vijay-to-become-the-highest-paid-indian-actor-with-pushpa-2/articleshow/114646487.cms |url-status=live }}</ref> directed by [[Sukumar]] and produced by [[Mythri Movie Makers]], in association with Sukumar Writings. The film stars [[Allu Arjun]] in the titular role, alongside [[Rashmika Mandanna]], [[Fahadh Faasil]], [[Jagapathi Babu]], [[Jagadeesh Prathap Bandari]], [[Dhananjaya (actor)|Dhananjaya]], [[Rao Ramesh]], [[Sunil (actor)|Sunil]], [[Anasuya Bharadwaj]] and [[Ajay (actor)|Ajay]]. It is the second instalment of the [[Pushpa (film series)|''Pushpa'' film series]] and the sequel to ''[[Pushpa: The Rise]]'' (2021). The film follows Pushpa Raj, a [[coolie]] risen to the ranks of sandalwood smuggler, who begins to face tough opposition from enemies, including [[Superintendent of police (India)|SP]] Bhanwar Singh Shekhawat [[Indian Police Service|IPS]].

